hackathon-description-text: Ever wondered what hackathons are all about are all about? Want to get your feet wet, see if you like it, before venturing into a bigger event? Interested in meeting local hackers, or in learning a new skill without having to risk getting an F in your class?

hackathon-judges.judge-role: Engineer, College Student, and Worked at Microsoft at 16

hackathon-eligibility: Has to be created within the time period of the hackathon. No previous work can be submitted. We are depending on integrity for this.
hackathon-rules: Follow the MLH rules for this hackathon.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Get your hands on an amazing Android Tablet.
Fly your way out of here.
Rock your soul out like Marley.

hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=10100 Finch Avenue, Cupertino, CA 95014, USA

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: The application or product should have a good aesthetic quality to it.
The product should be able to be appyled in the real world.
The project should demonstrate some level of technological complexity. The creator must explain what they learned in the process of creating their product.

hackathon-description-header: Cupertino High School's premier Hackathon. Show us all you got and code like never before.
